How long does it take to bring a new drug to market?
 
Johnson K. Gao
March 21, 2020
 
         On average, it takes at least ten years for a new medicine to complete the journey from initial discovery to the marketplace, with clinical trials alone taking six to seven years on average. The average cost to research and develop each successful drug is estimated to be $2.6 billion. See an article in detail. [1]
 
         Ten years to develop a new drug seems quite long. However, in compared with evolutionary scale, it is too short a time. The plant fern, such as wood fern Dryopteris, appeared on earth during the period of dinosaurs to live. [2]Some ferns are still living in the current world. They could be considered as living fossils. We know that dinosaurs lived in Jurassic Period (201 to 145 million years ago). During the Jurassic period, especially at higher latitudes, the warm, humid climate allowed lush jungles to cover much of the landscape. To my imagination the warm and humid climate is also favorable to germs to grow. In order not to let bacteria and virus damaging the body of the fern, fern must under went the natural selection process and to acquire the ability of producing antibiotics and antiviral substances. That is quite reasonable that Dryopteris root or fern rhizome, which has the Chinese herb name: 貫眾,has the characteristic of antibacterial, antiviral, anthelmintic. Please see “A review of the use of pteridophytes for treating human ailments”. See an article Anti-Influenza Virus (H5N1) Activity Screening on the Phloroglucinols from Rhizomes of Dryopteris crassirhizoma.[3]Use 10 (drug develop year needed)/145,000,000 (late Jurassic year) it produce 1/14,500,000. That means the ferns live now had spent 14.5 million times of drug development years needed to have invented the special antiviral “drug” in their root. Why don’t we use that drug to try to help us to anti corona virus and save the drug developmental time? Similarly, I had suggested using 板藍根(Radix Isatidis) to help us to anti coronavirus.
